## Summary of Testing Results

The inline month picker (Month Picker inline) in the ng2-date-picker-demo website has been tested for cross-year selection of the same month (August):

### Test Results: ✅ PASS

**Test Steps Performed:**
1. **Navigated to "Month Picker inline"** section in the left sidebar ✅
2. **Selected August 2017**: Navigated back 9 years to 2017, clicked "Aug" - it was highlighted with a blue circle ✅
3. **Switched to 2018 and selected August**: Clicked right arrow to go to 2018, then clicked "Aug" - it correctly updated the selection to August 2018 ✅
4. **Switched to 2019 and selected August**: Clicked right arrow to go to 2019, then clicked "Aug" - it correctly updated the selection to August 2019 ✅
5. **Verified cross-year behavior**: 
   - When viewing 2018 after selecting Aug 2019, no month was highlighted in 2018 ✅
   - When returning to 2019, "Aug" was still highlighted ✅

**Functional Behavior**: The inline month picker correctly handles cross-year selection of the same month. Each time a month is selected in a different year, the selection updates properly - only the most recently selected year+month combination is highlighted.

**Visual Observations**: 
- The inline month picker displays correctly with year navigation arrows
- Month selection is clearly indicated with a blue circle
- No visual anomalies detected in the picker component
- The page layout appears normal with Attribute options, Config options, and API sections below the picker
